==English==
===Etymology===
Greek ''holos'' "whole" + ''kaustos'' "burnt" <!-- Please clean up -->
Traditionally it referred to ritual sacrifice, as mentioned in Leviticus 4:7

===Noun===
'''holocaust''' (''plural'' '''holocausts''')

#A [[sacrifice]] that is completely burned to ashes.
#The state-sponsored mass murder of an ethnic group (see also the proper noun below).
#An atrocity committed on a group of people.

===Proper noun===
'''the Holocaust'''

#The mass murder of [[Jew]]s and other undesirables by the [[Nazi]] regime during [[World War II]].

